ecdc0ea0d7a6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the conjoint skeleton fully-contracted terms. At second \
order, transpositions between single particles of both different vertices \
(external permutations) and the same vertex (internal permutations) are \
possible. Fully-contracted terms which are mapped one another by the \
permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"45eab091-40fb-4bf4-b7f4-db5c123f1da6"],
 " factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox[
      RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7db010f6-7b77-4aaa-bf5d-a7d91ecdc016"],
 " interaction vertex. Simultaneously, diagrams which are mapped one another \
by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u, v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are also identified and summed, eventually canceling out the other ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"86449b34-bebe-4c2b-a35a-9742f041e00a"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "factor at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "tuvw"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "81d6508d-02a7-4648-8662-a74f2b80373b"],
 " interaction vertex. The procedure is repeated 2 times, assuming in the \
second case, a permutation of the indices of the two vertices. As a result, \
60 second-order conjoint skeleton fully-contracted terms are found."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8836806708732624`*^9, 3.883680671103075*^9}, {
   3.8836807100445924`*^9, 3.8836809748029747`*^9}, {3.88368106035993*^9, 
   3.88368123630155*^9}, {3.8884066008391533`*^9, 3.8884066027299986`*^9}, {
   3.8897788646156874`*^9, 3.8897788665710464`*^9}, {3.8926969246265383`*^9, 
   3.8926970411577735`*^9}, {3.892698767515374*^9, 3.8926988019171734`*^9}, {
   3.892698944167777*^9, 3.89269895025534*^9}, 3.897980551930337*^9, {
   3.9118989337632127`*^9, 3.9118991105611753`*^9}, {3.911899164309193*^9, 
   3.911899190598539*^9}, {3.9119021521938486`*^9, 3.9119021639529204`*^9}, {
   3.91190327426869*^9, 3.9119033058295913`*^9}, {3.911906807421135*^9, 
