Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Filtration of the fully-contracted terms", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.874644843789677*^9, 3.8746448545752873`*^9}, {
   3.883112065177337*^9, 3.883112118360941*^9}, {3.8831146011227875`*^9, 
   3.8831146201744213`*^9}, {3.883115184479356*^9, 3.8831151965813236`*^9}, {
   3.8884058729915524`*^9, 3.8884058731821747`*^9}, {3.892800153537215*^9, 
   3.8928001610648518`*^9}, {3.897041751372193*^9, 3.8970417738128204`*^9}, {
   3.8970432846114845`*^9, 3.897043286022911*^9}, 
   3.911883818478182*^9},ExpressionUUID->"e6616835-ef98-4b3f-94d1-\
27f65a10d21d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Filtration of the left-and-right-dressed disjoint direct fully-contracted \
terms. At second order, transpositions between single particles of both \
different vertices (external permutations) and the same vertex (internal \
permutations) are possible. Fully-contracted terms which are mapped one \
another by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["p \[RightTeeArrow] q, r \[RightTeeArrow] s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are identified and summed, eventually canceling out the factor ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"2", "!"}], ")"}], "2"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5a94bb51-e0ca-4be1-938e-3038dbb85bc9"],
 " at the denominator, arising from the partial antisymmetry of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox[
     RowBox[{" ", "V"}], "_"], "pqrs"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "005aabb0-52ba-475b-a3ec-50dde933a7a5"],
 " interaction vertex. Simultaneously, diagrams which are mapped one another \
by the permutation ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  and ",
 StyleBox["t \[RightTeeArrow] u, v \[RightTeeArrow] w",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " are also identified and summed, eventually canceling out the other ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
